# Installer-Centric Project Context

- This repository is a curl-installable tool with a script-first workflow.
- We develop and push changes here but do **not** install or run the tool in this workspace. Users install it on their own servers via the curl one-liner.
- Treat `install.sh`, `update.sh`, `uninstall.sh`, and `scripts/setup-domain.sh` as critical paths.
- Prioritize shell portability (especially macOS/BSD compatibility) and safe quoting in installer/update scripts.
- Preserve and validate credential generation/login behavior when changing setup or env generation logic.
- Ensure API/UI changes remain compatible with base-path slug deployments.
- Claude interactions use `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` (TypeScript) in streaming input mode, **not** the Claude Code CLI. See `src/lib/claude/sdk-provider.ts`.
- SDK sessions are long-lived: one `query()` call per session with an AsyncGenerator for multi-turn input. Do **not** call `query()` per message.
- `persistSession: false` and `settingSources: []` — we use SQLite for persistence and build system prompts ourselves. CLAUDE.md from `CLAUDE_PROJECT_ROOT` is read and appended by `system-prompt.ts`.
- Personality is per-session: users choose it in the New Session dialog, not in global settings. "Command Sandbox" toggle lives only in the Security > Command Sandbox sub-tab. Avoid re-introducing duplicate settings sections.
- **Always commit and push fixes.** Users install from `origin/main` via the curl one-liner, so local-only changes do nothing for them. After making a fix, immediately `git add`, `commit`, and `push` — don't leave fixes sitting as uncommitted changes.
